    <h3>2.1 Customer Website Layer & autoverse-agent Widget</h3>
    <p>
        The outermost layer consists of the **Customer Website** hosting the embedded **autoverse-agent widget**.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Decoupled NPM Module:</strong> The widget exists in its own separate workspace folder (<code>autoverse-agent/</code>) and is compiled into a lightweight client bundle with absolutely zero production dependencies. Building the script using <code>tsup</code> compiles all CSS, HTML nodes, and JS event-handling into a single, optimized 25 KB browser bundle (<code>dist/browser.mjs</code>).</li>
        <li><strong>Shadow DOM Isolation:</strong> When injected, the widget encapsulates its DOM tree within a Shadow Root, ensuring its styling properties never bleed into the host customer site, and protecting the widget itself from style contamination by external CSS frameworks (such as Tailwind or Bootstrap).</li>
        <li><strong>Main-Thread Protection:</strong> All client widget requests use asynchronous HTTP calls and run within a setTimeout tick, guaranteeing the widget never blocks host React rendering or page loads.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.2 api.autoverse.com Gateway Layer (autoverse-server)</h3>
    <p>
        The central nervous system of the project is the core backend API, hosted on **Railway** as **<code>api.autoverse.com</code>**.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Express.js API Router:</strong> Configured with strictly defined Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) rules to secure endpoints while allowing the widget to call them securely from authorized hostnames.</li>
        <li><strong>AI & RAG Inference Core:</strong> Houses the retrieval pipeline (Cheerio-based scraping, local vector similarity stores, and in-memory caches) and routes context-enriched prompts to Groq's high-speed LPU infrastructure.</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Widget Delivery:</strong> Exposes a GET route (<code>/autoverse/widget.js</code>) that compiles host and Bot ID configurations on the fly, allowing developers to embed the widget using a single, static script tag.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.3 Database Layer</h3>
    <p>
        The persistent storage layer sits between the dashboard and backend gateway, securing persistence of critical configurations and chat transcripts.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Decoupled Storage Operations:</strong> Separates read-heavy configuration retrieval from high-frequency write operations (chat transcripts) to protect configurations from database write-locks.</li>
        <li><strong>Centralized Integrity:</strong> Holds structured tables for bot appearances, tone settings, scraping indices, and visitor UUID tracking.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.4 Vercel Dashboard Layer</h3>
    <p>
        The administrative dashboard is a decoupled SPA built with React 18 and Vite, deployed on **Vercel's global Edge CDN** for instantaneous loading.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Autonomous Execution:</strong> The dashboard runs independently of the backend API server. It compiles statically and communicates securely with the API gateway using <code>import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL</code> environment variables.</li>
        <li><strong>Micro-Animation Engine:</strong> Uses CSS variables and state syncing to preview customizations (colors, border-radii, glassmorphism) instantly within an interactive preview simulator, without requiring database writes or page updates.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Major Features (Deep Dive)</h2>

    <h3>3.1 Automated Web Scraping & Ingestion</h3>
    <p>When a user creates a bot and provides a URL, the backend utilizes the <strong>Cheerio</strong> library to perform a deep scrape of the target website.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Text Extraction:</strong> Intelligently parses HTML to extract meaningful paragraphs, headings, and descriptions while ignoring navigational boilerplate.</li>
        <li><strong>Product Detection:</strong> Scans for e-commerce metadata (prices, inventory status, product images). If found, it categorizes these specifically as "products" in the vector store rather than standard text.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.2 Advanced Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)</h3>
    <p>Instead of relying on the AI's general knowledge (which causes hallucinations), the system uses RAG.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Vector Embeddings:</strong> Scraped content is converted into mathematical vectors.</li>
        <li><strong>Semantic Search:</strong> When a user asks a question, the system calculates the <em>cosine similarity</em> between the user's question and the stored vectors, retrieving only the most relevant paragraphs to feed to the LLM.</li>
        <li><strong>Response Caching:</strong> Frequently asked questions are cached in memory (<code>cache.ts</code>) to bypass the LLM API, reducing latency to near-zero and saving API costs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.3 Dynamic Persona & Contextual Adaptation</h3>
    <p>The system prompt is highly dynamic and generates rules on the fly based on the scraped data.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Portfolio/Service Mode:</strong> If the scraper finds no products (e.g., a CV or portfolio site), the AI adopts an informational, polite, and helpful persona, completely hiding any sales or shopping logic.</li>
        <li><strong>E-Commerce Mode:</strong> If products are detected, the AI injects special "E-Commerce Rules" into its brain. It learns to display products with images and prices, check inventory, and even execute a multi-step <strong>Order Automation Flow</strong> (collecting Name, Phone, Address, and Payment Method).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.4 Strict Multi-Lingual Enforcement</h3>
    <p>The agent is specifically engineered for the South Asian demographic, fully supporting English, Urdu, and Roman Urdu.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Anti-Code-Switching Logic:</strong> LLMs naturally tend to mix English and Roman Urdu. Autoverse implements strict prompt boundaries: If a user types in English (even a single word like "portfolio"), the AI locks into English. If they use Roman Urdu, it responds strictly in Roman Urdu.</li>
        <li><strong>Humanized Tone:</strong> Rules are in place to prevent the AI from sounding like a textbook or a dramatic poet (e.g., banning phrases like "Wahai dost" or "Assalamu alaikum" in English queries), forcing it to speak like a modern, casual Gen-Z/Millennial.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.5 Off-Topic Query Protection</h3>
    <p>The RAG pipeline contains strict refusal mechanisms. If a user asks about coding, math, general science, or historical facts unrelated to the website, the AI politely refuses to answer, protecting the brand's identity and saving API tokens.</p>

    <h2>4. Minor Features & Granular Customizations</h2>
    
    <h3>4.1 UI & Appearance Settings</h3>
    <p>The dashboard provides granular control over the widget's look and feel:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Colors:</strong> Custom Primary and Accent color pickers.</li>
        <li><strong>Positioning:</strong> Toggle between Bottom-Left and Bottom-Right screen placement.</li>
        <li><strong>Sizing:</strong> Adjustable chat bubble sizes (Small, Medium, Large).</li>
        <li><strong>Border Radius:</strong> Sharp edges, rounded corners, or pill-shaped designs.</li>
        <li><strong>Modern Effects:</strong> Toggles for <em>Glassmorphism</em> (translucent, blurred backgrounds), Shadow Intensity (Low, Medium, High), and Button Variants (Solid, Outline, Ghost).</li>
        <li><strong>Dual-Color Gradients:</strong> Option to enable vibrant gradient headers using the primary and accent colors.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.2 Chat History & Session Management</h3>
    <p>Data persistence and monitoring for administrators:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Session Tracking:</strong> Every unique visitor is assigned a UUID, and their conversation history is persistently saved to <code>history.json</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Transcript Viewing:</strong> Admins can read full chat logs in the dashboard to understand customer needs.</li>
        <li><strong>Granular Deletion:</strong> Implemented REST API endpoints allowing admins to delete specific spam/test sessions individually.</li>
        <li><strong>Bulk Clear:</strong> A "Clear All History" feature to wipe the bot's memory entirely.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.3 Tone & Prompt Configuration</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Custom Instructions:</strong> Admins can inject specific rules (e.g., "Always greet the user with 'Howdy Partner'").</li>
        <li><strong>Response Length:</strong> Settings to force the AI to be concise (Short), balanced (Medium), or highly detailed (Long).</li>
    </ul>

